# HAYC Config Pattern

This project uses a remote config system. All user-facing text and images must go through the HAYC helpers. Never hardcode text or image paths directly in JSX.

## Critical Setup (Do First!)

### 1. Wrap App with HaycProvider
The `HaycProvider` MUST wrap the entire app in `App.tsx`. Without this, any component using `useHayc()` will crash with "useHayc must be used inside HaycProvider".

```tsx
// src/App.tsx
import { HaycProvider } from './hayc/config-context';

function App() {
  return (
    <HaycProvider>
      <BrowserRouter>
        {/* ... routes ... */}
      </BrowserRouter>
    </HaycProvider>
  );
}
```

### 2. Install Required Dependencies
Before running the app, ensure these common dependencies are installed:
```bash
npm install react-router-dom
```
Do not remove anything from package.json, just additions

### 3. Populate Config Values with Actual Content
When adding fields to `config.ts`, do NOT leave them as empty strings:
```tsx
// ❌ Wrong — will render nothing
brandName: { el: '', en: '' },

// ✅ Correct — populate with actual content
brandName: { el: 'Portfolio', en: 'Portfolio' },
```

## Rules

### 1. Always import and call useHayc
Every component in `src/sections/`, `src/components/`, and `src/pages/` must:
```tsx
import { useHayc } from '../hayc/config-context';

const { t, img, config, cp } = useHayc();
```

### 2. All text must use t()
Never render a LocaleString object directly. Always wrap with t():
```tsx
// ❌ Wrong
<h1>{config.heroConfig.mainTitle}</h1>

// ✅ Correct
<h1>{t(config.heroConfig.mainTitle)}</h1>
```

### 3. All image paths must use img()
```tsx
// ❌ Wrong
<img src={config.heroConfig.backgroundImage} />

// ✅ Correct
<img src={img(config.heroConfig.backgroundImage)} />
```

### 4. No hardcoded user-facing strings in JSX
Any string a user can read must live in config.ts as a LocaleString:
```tsx
// ❌ Wrong
<div className="text-xs">View All</div>

// ✅ Correct — add to config.ts first, then:
<div className="text-xs">{t(config.featuredProjectsConfig.viewAllButton)}</div>
```

### 5. Adding new content to config.ts
When a component needs a new text field:
- Add the field to the correct interface in config.ts as `LocaleString`
- Add the value to the config object with ACTUAL content: `{ el: 'Greek text', en: 'English text' }`
- Use `t()` in the component
- **IMPORTANT:** Never leave values as empty strings — the UI will be blank!

### 6. Adding new image fields to config.ts
- Add the field as plain `string` (not LocaleString)
- Add the value with the actual image URL/path (not empty string)
- Use `img()` in the component

### 7. Fields that stay as plain string (never LocaleString)
- Image paths
- Icon names (e.g. "MapPin", "Instagram")
- href / anchor values
- id fields
- CSS filter values
- formEndpoint, newsletterEndpoint, canonical, ogImage
- glowColor, filter, language

